		<div id="comment_body_64701040"><p>I've actually decided that I quite like self checkout (assuming that it's working correctly, which is by no means a given) because you can check the prices as you go.</p><p>When the cashier does it she goes zip zip zip zip and you have no idea if you're paying $4.95 or $14.95 for that last item.</p><p>With self checkout you scan stuff at your own speed and when you see an incorrect price you can stop and say, "Hey, there's a problem here."</p><p>A lot of store receipts (looking at you, Walmart) don't actually say what each item<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64701040">

</div>
